<plot>Gina and Seth (Marla Sokoloff and Patrick J. Adams) became pen pals 13 years ago in a class assignment. Gina lives in Boston now and finds out Seth will be in town for a toy conference she is going to cover for her paper. They both had sent pictures of their best friends, Ellen and Matt (Lindy Booth and Jonathan Cherry) to each other instead. Now Gina and Seth force their best friends to meet as them. Unfortunately for them both, Ellen and Matt start to fall for each other. About half-way through, the real Seth figures out that the girl reporter he has been talking to is really Gina. In the end, Gina finds out the truth and they finally kiss.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?105010</url></doc>
